==English==
===Etymology===
A jocular coinage, apparently by students at Eton, combining a number of roughly synonymous Latin stems.  Latin ''flocci'', from ''[[floccus]]'', a wisp or piece of wool + ''nauci'', from ''[[naucum]]'', a trifle + ''nihili'', from ''[[nihilum]]'', nothing + ''pili'', from ''[[pilus]]'', a hair, something insignificant (all therefore having the sense of "worthless" or "nothing") + [[-fication]].

